messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Do you need police or paramedic?
Yes.
No, I want to report a drug overdose.
Who had a drug overdose?
Pardon?
Who had a drug overdose?
Oh, this girl I'm...
Okay, is she there with you?
Yeah, she's in my son's room.
Okay, where are you?
Okay, we're at Ardell Drive. Palm Beach Gardens, Florida, 33410.
Give me one moment, okay?
Yes.
What did she overdose with?
I don't know.
Can you confirm the address of your emergency?
That's going to be Ardell Drive.
And what's wrong?
It's going to be a drug overdose.
What's her name?
Pardon?
What's the female's name?
Anastasia.
How old is she?
I think she's 18, 19, something like that.
Is she awake?
Oh, no, I think she's dead.
Is she cold to the touch?
Yeah, yeah, I think so. I'm pretty distraught over this whole thing.
I understand. When was the last time she was seen?

Well, it's like she was here yesterday, and, you know, her car was parked here, and she was supposedly sleeping in my son's room. And I guess he got panicky because she passed away. And so she just passed away yesterday. And I found out just about an hour ago, and I've been in a panic ever since.
This is your daughter?
No, this is not mine. That's somebody else. That's my son. He got scared.
So it's an acquaintance of your son?
Yeah.
I understand. It's just terrible. I don't know what to say. I'm just my wife, and I just don't know what to do.
I understand. All right.
We'll have a unit on the way. You're pretty sure she's gone.
Oh, yeah. She's...
I understand. I'm sorry you're in this predicament. I just don't, you know, it's like my whole life is over now. I don't know.
But you know what to say. You know, I don't know what to do.
We're going to send the people over there to help you. We'll be right there.
Okay. Just make sure to do it. You know what's that now.
Is this Waterway Manor?
Yes, it is. That's right. It's off of Palmwood.
All right. And is this a house or an apartment?
No, it's a house.
All right. The police are on the way.
Okay. Thank you. Bye-bye.
